    <stitle>Spanish - Gu&#237;a para Localizaci&#243;n de Fallas del Sistema El&#233;ctrico - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400,
        7300, 7400, 7500, 8500, 8600 - STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY, TILT - 9600, 9700, 9800 - DISASSEMBLE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DISASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="4">
            <title>TILT MECHANISM</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the locking nut and double nut retainer of the tilt control lever (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0501015">Figure 15</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0501015" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0501015" filename="../figg05/G0501015.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 12. Tilt Mechanism Lever Removal</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To further disassemble the tilt mechanism, remove the right selector bracket. Compress
                    the tilt lever tension spring and remove the retaining ring (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0501016">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0501016" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0501016" filename="../figg05/G0501016.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 13. Tilt Mechanism Retaining Ring Removal</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To remove the tilt lever and tilt lever cam, use a punch and remove two (2) roll pins (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0501017">Figure 17</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0501017" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0501017" filename="../figg05/G0501017.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 14. Tilt Lever, Cam and Roller Pin Removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. TILT LEVER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. TILT CAM</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. ROLL PINS</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. SELECTOR BRACKET</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent eye injury, safety glasses should be worn at all times when assembling or
                        disassembling components.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the tilt lever, tilt cam, spring washers, and special washer from the positioning
                    pin. Remove the positioning pin, then the selector bracket can be removed (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0501018">Figure 18</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0501018" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0501018" filename="../figg05/G0501018.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 15. Selector Pin Removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. TILT LEVER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. TILT CAM</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SPRING WASHERS</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. SPECIAL WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. BRACKET WITH BUSHING</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. POSITIONING PIN</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
